Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @potatoes{450%g} into 2cm wide wedges (no need to peel). Put the wedges onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{10%ml}, season with @salt{} and @black pepper{}, then toss to coat.

Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-35%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @garlic clove{1} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Heat a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat (no oil).

Once hot, add the @British beef mince{240%g} and fry until browned, ~{5-6%minutes}. Once the mince has been in the pan for ~{2%minutes}, add the @diced chorizo{90%g} and fry until both start to brown, ~{3-4%minutes}. Use a #spoon{} to break up the mince as it cooks, then drain and discard any excess fat.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince.

Once the mince and chorizo are browned, add the @Mexican style spice mix{1%tbsp} (add less if you'd prefer things milder) and garlic to the pan and cook for ~{2-3%minutes}.

Add the @tomato passata{1%400g can}, @water for the sauce{100%ml} and @beef stock paste{10%g}. Stir and bring to the boil, then reduce the heat.

Simmer, stirring occasionally, until the sauce is thick, ~{10-12%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The mince is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, drain and rinse the @black beans{1%400g can} in a #sieve{}.

Halfway through simmering, stir the beans into the beef and chorizo mixture.

While the sauce thickens, grate the @mature cheddar cheese{30%g}.

When everything's ready, taste and season the beef and chorizo mixture with @salt{} and @pepper{} if needed.

Share the wedges between your #plates{}, then top with the beef - wedges loaded!

Scatter with the cheese and top with a dollop of @soured cream{75%g} to finish.

Enjoy!